{
  "texts": [
    "However, the efficiency of employing such basic structures in scene classification is restricted due to the massive scale and sophisticated content of image classification in remote sensing, as well as their features of minimum inter-class variety and tremendous inter-class variability.Authors in [19] introduced a new image classification strategy based on spatial scale CNN blocks that help in extracting and adaptively adjusting abundant spatial features to enhance the informative features function in the classification results.",
    "In [20], the authors proposed a bilinear CNN-based feature extraction structure to improve the classification accuracy, and they used a depthwise separable convolution to solve the computation complexity and volume.",
    "A lightweight deep network is suggested in [21] for remote sensing images by incorporating the benefits of multidilation pooling and the dilated convolution in MobileNet V2 network, extracting multiscale features and improving the classification accuracy.",
    "In [22], the authors focus on the image texture features instead of the single CNN layer features, and they presented a new coding strategy to extract each convolutional layer information, including global, local, bottom, and deep.",
    "Authors in [23] extract both local & global features from the spatial domain and rotation invariant features from the frequency domain, using a new joint learning module including CNN and bandpass filtering network.CNN-based algorithms have received massive interest in recent years, and their feature maps can reflect the scenes and achieve good classification performance [24]."
  ]
}